7:
This rule applies to all HTML elements with the class "alert"

The word "class" is a new concept for you. 

Class is an attribute we can add to HTML tags in order to style a specific grup of elements.
(Sınıf, belirli bir öğe grubuna stil vermek için HTML etiketlerine ekleyebileceğimiz bir niteliktir.)

"class" allows(ılauz) us to separate elements of the same tag into different groups.
("class" ayni tag'dan olusan elementleri, farkli gruplara ayirmamizi saglar.)

11:
"class" is a keyword of css and it does not change.
but "alert" is a value and you can change it to any word you want.

We can add the same "class" and its value to multiple same and different tags.
(ayni "class" ve deferini birden cok ayni ve farkli taglara ekleyebiliriz.)

What did I do in this example?
using class value, I grouped multiple same tags.

14:
This rule applies to only <p> elements with the class "alert"
If you put p before (.), it means tag name should be p, class value should "alert"

16:
The "class" attribute can have multiple values. 
And there should be a space between these values.

